  <chapter number="10" style="c" sid="MRK 10" />
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="1" style="v" sid="MRK 10:1" />He headed out from there and went to the Judean area, on the other side of the Jordan <char style="it">River</char>,
        and a crowd gathered around him again, and he began teaching them again per usual. <verse eid="MRK 10:1" />
      <verse number="2" style="v" sid="MRK 10:2" /><char style="it">Some</char> Pharisees went up to him and started asking if it’s legal<char style="sup">[A]</char>
        for a husband to divorce his wife,<char style="sup">[a]</char> trying to catch him in a mistake. <verse eid="MRK 10:2" />
      <verse number="3" style="v" sid="MRK 10:3" />His reply to them was, <char style="wj">“What does the Old Testament</char><char style="sup">[b]</char><char
        style="wj"> command you to do?” </char><verse eid="MRK 10:3" />
      <verse number="4" style="v" sid="MRK 10:4" />They said, “The Old Testament allows you ‘…to write a divorce certificate and cut <char style="it">her
        </char>loose’<char style="sup">[c]</char>.” <verse eid="MRK 10:4" />
      <verse number="5" style="v" sid="MRK 10:5" />Jesus said, <char style="wj">“This commandment, when written, was </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">directed</char></char><char
        style="wj"> towards your hard-heartedness.</char><char style="sup">[d]</char><char style="wj"> </char><verse eid="MRK 10:5" />
      <verse number="6" style="v" sid="MRK 10:6" /><char style="wj">But from the beginning of creation, ‘He made them man and woman, husband and wife</char><char
        style="sup">[e]</char><char style="wj">. </char><verse eid="MRK 10:6" />
      <verse number="7" style="v" sid="MRK 10:7" /><char style="wj">On account of this, a man shall leave behind his mother and father and shall stick to
        his woman, his wife</char><char style="sup">[f]</char><char style="wj">, </char><verse eid="MRK 10:7" />
      <verse number="8" style="v" sid="MRK 10:8" /><char style="wj">and the two will be </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">made</char></char><char
        style="wj"> into one flesh, resulting in their no longer being two </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">individual
        fleshes</char></char><char style="wj"> but one flesh</char><char style="sup">[g]</char><char style="wj">.’
        </char><verse eid="MRK 10:8" />
      <verse number="9" style="v" sid="MRK 10:9" /><char style="wj">That which God joined let no person separate.”</char> <verse eid="MRK 10:9" />
      <verse number="10" style="v" sid="MRK 10:10" />When they got back home again, the disciples asked him about this. <verse eid="MRK 10:10" />
      <verse number="11" style="v" sid="MRK 10:11" />He tells them, <char style="wj">“Whoever cuts his wife loose (</char><char style="it"><char style="wj">i.e.,
        divorces her</char></char><char style="wj">) and marries another </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">woman
        </char></char><char style="wj">commits adultery with</char><char style="sup">[h]</char><char style="wj">
        her, </char><verse eid="MRK 10:11" />
      <verse number="12" style="v" sid="MRK 10:12" /><char style="wj">and if she, having been cut loose from her husband, marries another, she commits adultery.”</char><verse eid="MRK 10:12" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="13" style="v" sid="MRK 10:13" />They brought children to him for him to affect through touch, but his disciples scolded them. <verse eid="MRK 10:13" />
      <verse number="14" style="v" sid="MRK 10:14" />Seeing this, Jesus became indignant and said to them, <char style="wj">“Evermore let the children come
        to me, and don’t get in their way, since whom God interacts with (God’s kingdom) is </char><char style="it"><char
        style="wj">drawn</char></char><char style="wj"> from such as these. </char><verse eid="MRK 10:14" />
      <verse number="15" style="v" sid="MRK 10:15" /><char style="wj">Let me tell you what: whoever won’t receive God’s kingdom like a child </char><char
        style="it"><char style="wj">would, </char></char><char style="wj">certainly won’t enter it.”</char> <verse eid="MRK 10:15" />
      <verse number="16" style="v" sid="MRK 10:16" />He put his arms around them and pronounced a blessing over them while laying his hands on them.<verse eid="MRK 10:16" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="17" style="v" sid="MRK 10:17" />While venturing out on the road, someone ran up, fell to his knees before him, and asked him,
    </para>
    <para style="p" vid="MRK 10:17">“Good teacher, what do I have to do to lay claim to that special fullness of life (eternal life)?”<verse eid="MRK 10:17"/>
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="18" style="v" sid="MRK 10:18" />Jesus said, “Why do you call me ‘good’?<char style="sup">[B]</char> Nobody’s good except for one <char
        style="it">person</char>: God. <verse eid="MRK 10:18" />
      <verse number="19" style="v" sid="MRK 10:19" />You know the commandments…do not murder…do not commit adultery…don’t steal…don’t lie when called on to
        make a statement for the record…don’t rip each other off<char style="sup">[i]</char>…honor your mother
        and father.”<verse eid="MRK 10:19" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="20" style="v" sid="MRK 10:20" />So he said, “Teacher, I’ve been vigilant to keep all of these since I was a teenager.”<verse eid="MRK 10:20" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="21" style="v" sid="MRK 10:21" />So Jesus stared at him and felt an appreciation for the great value of his life<char style="sup">[j]</char>
        and said, <char style="wj">“You’re missing one piece: go out and sell what you have and give it to the
        poor, and you’ll have treasure in heaven, and come </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">back</char></char><char
        style="wj"> to this spot and be my follower.”</char><verse eid="MRK 10:21" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="22" style="v" sid="MRK 10:22" />Now he became melancholy over this remark and departed with a sulk, since he owned a lot of stuff<char
        style="sup">[k]</char>. <verse eid="MRK 10:22" />
      <verse number="23" style="v" sid="MRK 10:23" />Jesus looked around and mused to his disciples, <char style="wj">“How difficult indeed it is for someone
        who owns a lot of stuff to have God interact with him (enter God’s kingdom).”</char> <verse eid="MRK 10:23" />
      <verse number="24" style="v" sid="MRK 10:24" />His disciples were simply stunned by this statement. But again Jesus, from out of his contemplation,
        said to them, <char style="wj">“Boys</char><char style="sup">[l]</char><char style="wj">, how difficult
        it is to enter God’s kingdom. </char><verse eid="MRK 10:24" />
      <verse number="25" style="v" sid="MRK 10:25" /><char style="wj">It’s easier for a camel to crouch down and crawl through a small gate portal</char><char
        style="sup">[m]</char><char style="wj"> than for a rich person to enter God’s kingdom.” </char><verse eid="MRK 10:25" />
      <verse number="26" style="v" sid="MRK 10:26" />But still in a state of shock, they say to one another, “And how can anyone be kept <char style="it">from
        this</char><char style="sup">[n]</char>?” <verse eid="MRK 10:26" />
      <verse number="27" style="v" sid="MRK 10:27" />Jesus stared at them and declares, <char style="wj">“With people, it’s not possible—certainly not without
        God; for all things are possible with God.” </char><verse eid="MRK 10:27" />
      <verse number="28" style="v" sid="MRK 10:28" />Peter proceeded to say to him, “Look—we for our part left everything so that we could become your followers.”<verse eid="MRK 10:28" />
      <verse number="29" style="v" sid="MRK 10:29" />Jesus said, <char style="wj">“I’m telling you for sure: nobody who’s left </char><char style="it"><char
        style="wj">his</char></char><char style="wj"> home or </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">his</char></char><char
        style="wj"> brother or sister or mother or father or child or livelihood on account of me and on account
        of the Good News</char><char style="sup">[o]</char><char style="wj"> </char><verse eid="MRK 10:29" />
      <verse number="30" style="v" sid="MRK 10:30" /><char style="wj">will fail to receive big time</char><char style="sup">[p]</char><char style="wj">—right
        now in this present age—homes, brothers, sisters, mothers, children, livelihoods—along with persecution,
        and that special fullness of life (eternal life) in the age to come. </char><verse eid="MRK 10:30" />
      <verse number="31" style="v" sid="MRK 10:31" /><char style="wj">And many </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">who are</char></char><char style="wj">
        first will be last and last first.”</char><verse eid="MRK 10:31" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="32" style="v" sid="MRK 10:32" />They were on their way over to Jerusalem, and Jesus was leading the pack. They were all the while stunned:
        those following <char style="it">his lead</char> were in a state of fear. Confiding in the Twelve, he
        began to go over with them what would happen to him, the things<char style="it"> in motion </char>that
        were converging. <verse eid="MRK 10:32" />
      <verse number="33" style="v" sid="MRK 10:33" /><char style="wj">”…Because, you see, we’re going to Jerusalem, and the Man</char><char style="sup">[q]</char><char
        style="wj"> will be apprehended by the chief priests and the designated teachers</char><char style="sup">[r]</char><char
        style="wj">, they’ll sentence him to death, and hand him over to the Gentiles. </char><verse eid="MRK 10:33" />
      <verse number="34" style="v" sid="MRK 10:34" /><char style="wj">They’ll make fun of him, spit on him, flog him, and kill him, and after three days,
        he’ll be resurrected.”</char><verse eid="MRK 10:34" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="35" style="v" sid="MRK 10:35" />James and John, the sons of Zebedee, wandered over to him and said to him,
    </para>
    <para style="p" vid="MRK 10:35">“Teacher, we want to ask a favor of you.”<verse eid="MRK 10:35"/>
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="36" style="v" sid="MRK 10:36" />He said, <char style="wj">“What do you want me to do for you?”</char><verse eid="MRK 10:36" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="37" style="v" sid="MRK 10:37" />They said, “Let one of us be your number-one man and the other your number-two when you’re invested in
        your regal power.<char style="sup">[s]</char>”<verse eid="MRK 10:37" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="38" style="v" sid="MRK 10:38" />Jesus said, <char style="wj">“You don’t have any idea what you’re asking for. Can you go through what
        I have to go through or get in up to your neck in the same things I have to?</char><char style="sup">[t]</char><char
        style="wj">”</char><verse eid="MRK 10:38" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="39" style="v" sid="MRK 10:39" />They said, “We can.”
    </para>
    <para style="p" vid="MRK 10:39">Jesus said, <char style="wj">“What I’ll go through, so will you, and what I’ll be up to my neck in, so
        will you.</char><char style="sup">[t]</char><char style="wj"> </char><verse eid="MRK 10:39"/>
      <verse number="40" style="v" sid="MRK 10:40" /><char style="wj">But to be my number-one or number-two man is not for me to grant, but is </char><char
        style="it"><char style="wj">reserved</char></char><char style="wj"> for those for whom it has been prepared.”</char><verse eid="MRK 10:40" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="41" style="v" sid="MRK 10:41" />Once they heard about this, the ten became furious with James and John. <verse eid="MRK 10:41" />
      <verse number="42" style="v" sid="MRK 10:42" />Jesus called them over and tells them, <char style="wj">“You’re aware that those considered to be leaders
        of the peoples throughout the earth subjugate the populace, and their chiefs</char><char style="sup">[C]</char><char
        style="wj">, </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">filled with charisma and valor</char></char><char
        style="wj">, maintain absolute authority over them. </char><verse eid="MRK 10:42" />
      <verse number="43" style="v" sid="MRK 10:43" /><char style="wj">But it will not be this way among you; instead, whoever would desire to be a </char><char
        style="it"><char style="wj">charismatic, valor-filled</char></char><char style="wj"> chief among you
        will be everyone’s servant</char><char style="sup">[u]</char><char style="wj">, </char><verse eid="MRK 10:43" />
      <verse number="44" style="v" sid="MRK 10:44" /><char style="wj">and whoever would desire to be number-one among you will be everyone’s servant, </char><verse eid="MRK 10:44" />
      <verse number="45" style="v" sid="MRK 10:45" /><char style="wj">seeing that the Man didn’t come to be served either, but instead to serve and to give
        his life-being as a ransom payment to ransom the many.”</char><verse eid="MRK 10:45" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="46" style="v" sid="MRK 10:46" />They came to Jericho, and while he, his disciples, and a sizeable crowd were departing Jericho, the son
        of Timaeus, Bartimaeus<char style="sup">[D]</char> <char style="it">by name</char>, a blind beggar, was
        sitting alongside the road. <verse eid="MRK 10:46" />
      <verse number="47" style="v" sid="MRK 10:47" />Having heard that Jesus of Nazareth was <char style="it">the reason for the crowd</char>, he began to
        cry out repeatedly, saying,</para>
    <para style="p" vid="MRK 10:47">“Jesus, you marvelous godsend<char style="sup">[v]</char>, have pity on me!”<verse eid="MRK 10:47"/>
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="48" style="v" sid="MRK 10:48" />Many scolded him to hush him up, but he cried out all the more, “You marvelous godsend, have pity on
        me!”<verse eid="MRK 10:48" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="49" style="v" sid="MRK 10:49" />Jesus stood still and said, <char style="wj">“Call him </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">over</char></char><char
        style="wj">.”</char></para>
    <para style="p" vid="MRK 10:49">They called for the blind man, saying to him, “Brace yourself<char style="sup">[w]</char>—get up, he’s
        calling you.”<verse eid="MRK 10:49"/>
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="50" style="v" sid="MRK 10:50" />He threw off his cloak,<char style="sup">[E]</char> shot up, and went to Jesus. <verse eid="MRK 10:50" />
      <verse number="51" style="v" sid="MRK 10:51" />Jesus answered, <char style="wj">“What can I do for you?”</char>
    </para>
    <para style="p" vid="MRK 10:51">The blind man said, “Teacher—<char style="it">I just want </char>to see again<char style="sup">[F]</char>.”<verse eid="MRK 10:51"/>
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="52" style="v" sid="MRK 10:52" />Jesus said, <char style="wj">“Get going now, your faith has pulled you through</char><char style="sup">[x]</char><char
        style="wj">.” </char>Immediately, he regained his sight and took to the road, as he started being his
        follower.<verse eid="MRK 10:52" />
    </para>
