  <chapter number="11" style="c" sid="MRK 11" />
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="1" style="v" sid="MRK 11:1" />When they neared Jerusalem, arriving at<char style="it"> </char>Bethphage and Bethany at the Mount of
        Olives, he sent out two of his disciples. <verse eid="MRK 11:1" />
      <verse number="2" style="v" sid="MRK 11:2" />He, giving instructions, says to them, <char style="wj">“Go over to the town across the way from where
        you’re at, and as you go in, immediately you’ll find a colt which no person has ever mounted tied down.
        Untie it and start bringing it</char><char style="it"><char style="wj"> back</char></char><char style="wj">.
        </char><verse eid="MRK 11:2" />
      <verse number="3" style="v" sid="MRK 11:3" /><char style="wj">If anyone says to you, ‘Why are you doing this?’ Say, ‘His master needs it,’ and bring
        it back here right away.</char>” <verse eid="MRK 11:3" />
      <verse number="4" style="v" sid="MRK 11:4" />They left and found a colt tied to a gate which was up against the street, and they untied it. <verse eid="MRK 11:4" />
      <verse number="5" style="v" sid="MRK 11:5" />Some people who were standing there proceeded to tell them, “What are you doing, untying the colt?” <verse eid="MRK 11:5" />
      <verse number="6" style="v" sid="MRK 11:6" />They told them what Jesus said, and they left them alone. <verse eid="MRK 11:6" />
      <verse number="7" style="v" sid="MRK 11:7" />They <char style="it">then </char>bring the colt to Jesus, toss their outer garments on it, and he mounted
        it. <verse eid="MRK 11:7" />
      <verse number="8" style="v" sid="MRK 11:8" />Many people spread their outer garments out on the road, and others spread tall grass out, which was
        chopped down <char style="it">and brought over </char>from the fields. <verse eid="MRK 11:8" />
      <verse number="9" style="v" sid="MRK 11:9" />Those preceding and those following kept on shouting out,
    </para>
    <para style="pi" vid="MRK 11:9"></para>
    <para style="pi" vid="MRK 11:9">Rescue us<char style="sup">[a]</char>!</para>
    <para style="pi" vid="MRK 11:9">Praise be to him who comes at the Lord’s behest.<verse eid="MRK 11:9"/>
    </para>
    <para style="pi">
      <verse number="10" style="v" sid="MRK 11:10" />Praise be to the coming monarchy of our patriarch David.
    </para>
    <para style="pi" vid="MRK 11:10">Rescue us to the max!<verse eid="MRK 11:10"/>
    </para>
    <para style="pi" />    <!-- Spacer line. No verse associated with it. -->
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="11" style="v" sid="MRK 11:11" />He entered Jerusalem and went into the temple <char style="it">complex </char>and looked around at everything.
        It being late in the day already, he departed with the Twelve for Bethany. <verse eid="MRK 11:11" />
      <verse number="12" style="v" sid="MRK 11:12" />The next day, while they were leaving Bethany, <verse eid="MRK 11:12" />
      <verse number="13" style="v" sid="MRK 11:13" />seeing from a distance a fig tree that was in leaf, he went <char style="it">over to it</char>, if perchance
        he would find anything <char style="it">nestled</char> in it, and when he got up close to it, he found
        nothing except for leaves, since figs weren’t in season.<char style="sup">[A]</char> <verse eid="MRK 11:13" />
      <verse number="14" style="v" sid="MRK 11:14" />He considered <char style="it">the situation</char> and said, <char style="wj">“No longer—forever and
        ever—will anyone eat fruit which you’ve yielded.”</char> And his disciples were listening <char style="it">when
        he said it</char>.<verse eid="MRK 11:14" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="15" style="v" sid="MRK 11:15" />They <char style="it">then </char>come to Jerusalem. After entering the temple <char style="it">complex</char>,
        he began to throw out the salesmen and the merchandisers doing business in the temple, and he turned
        over the tables of the money changers and of those who were seated selling doves.<char style="sup">[B]</char><verse eid="MRK 11:15" />
      <verse number="16" style="v" sid="MRK 11:16" />He wasn’t letting anyone transport boxes<char style="sup">[b]</char> <char style="it">containing merchandise
        </char>through the temple. <verse eid="MRK 11:16" />
      <verse number="17" style="v" sid="MRK 11:17" />He was going about instructing them and, as part of doing so, said to them, <char style="wj">“Has it
        not been written in the Scriptures, ‘My house shall be called a house of prayer among all the nations’?—But
        you have made it into a robber’s hideout</char><char style="sup">[C]</char><char style="wj">.” </char><verse eid="MRK 11:17" />
      <verse number="18" style="v" sid="MRK 11:18" />The chief priests and the designated teachers<char style="sup">[c]</char> heard <char style="it">about
        this </char>and were trying to find a way they could eliminate him; the fact was, the crowd was amazed
        at his teaching. <verse eid="MRK 11:18" />
      <verse number="19" style="v" sid="MRK 11:19" />He was in the habit of leaving the city when evening arrived.<verse eid="MRK 11:19" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="20" style="v" sid="MRK 11:20" />Passing by in the morning, they saw the fig tree shriveled up from the roots <char style="it">on up</char>.<verse eid="MRK 11:20" />
      <verse number="21" style="v" sid="MRK 11:21" />Peter recalled <char style="it">the incident</char> and <char style="it">as a result </char>says, “Teacher,
        look—the fig tree which you cursed is all shriveled up.” <verse eid="MRK 11:21" />
      <verse number="22" style="v" sid="MRK 11:22" />Jesus, considering what happened, replied to them, <char style="wj">“Have the God-kind of faith</char><char
        style="sup">[d]</char><char style="wj">.</char><char style="sup">[D]</char><char style="sup">[E]</char><char
        style="wj"> </char><verse eid="MRK 11:22" />
      <verse number="23" style="v" sid="MRK 11:23" /><char style="wj">I’m telling you the truth—if someone were to speak to this mountain, ‘Be lifted up and
        thrown into the sea,’ and would not doubt</char><char style="sup">[d]</char><char style="wj"> in his
        heart but instead would believe</char><char style="sup">[d]</char><char style="wj"> that that which he
        says is coming to pass, it will be </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">that way</char></char><char
        style="wj"> with him. </char><verse eid="MRK 11:23" />
      <verse number="24" style="v" sid="MRK 11:24" /><char style="wj">On account of this, I say to you: all things which you all ask for in prayer</char><char
        style="sup">[e]</char><char style="wj">, believe</char><char style="sup">[d]</char><char style="wj">
        that you have received</char><char style="sup">[E]</char><char style="sup">[F]</char><char style="wj">,
        and it will be </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">that way</char></char><char style="wj"> with
        you. </char><verse eid="MRK 11:24" />
      <verse number="25" style="v" sid="MRK 11:25" /><char style="wj">And when you’re standing up praying, if you have something against someone, forgive,
        so that our Father in heaven would forgive you of your sins.”</char> <verse eid="MRK 11:25" />
      <verse number="26" style="v" sid="MRK 11:26" /><char style="sup">[G]</char><verse eid="MRK 11:26" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="27" style="v" sid="MRK 11:27" />He went to Jerusalem again. While he was walking about the temple <char style="it">compound</char>, the
        chief priests, the designated teachers, and the councilmen<char style="sup">[f]</char> approached him.<verse eid="MRK 11:27" />
      <verse number="28" style="v" sid="MRK 11:28" />They started speaking to him,
    </para>
    <para style="p" vid="MRK 11:28">“By what authority do you do these things? In other words, who gave you the authority to do these things?”<verse eid="MRK 11:28"/>
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="29" style="v" sid="MRK 11:29" />Jesus said, <char style="wj">“You answer my question, and I’ll answer yours.</char><char style="sup">[g]</char><char
        style="wj"> </char><verse eid="MRK 11:29" />
      <verse number="30" style="v" sid="MRK 11:30" /><char style="wj">John’s baptism: was </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">his authority to baptize
        derived</char></char><char style="wj"> from heaven</char><char style="sup">[h]</char><char style="wj">
        or from mankind?—Answer me.”</char><verse eid="MRK 11:30" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="31" style="v" sid="MRK 11:31" />They talked it over amongst themselves, saying, “If we say ‘From heaven’, he’ll say, ‘Then why didn’t
        you believe in him?’ <verse eid="MRK 11:31" />
      <verse number="32" style="v" sid="MRK 11:32" />But if we say, ‘From mankind,’…”—They feared the crowd, since everyone considered John to be a prophet.<verse eid="MRK 11:32" />
      <verse number="33" style="v" sid="MRK 11:33" />They answered Jesus, “We don’t know.”
    </para>
    <para style="p" vid="MRK 11:33">And Jesus <char style="it">then </char>tells them, <char style="wj">“Nor will I tell you by what authority
        I do these things.”</char><verse eid="MRK 11:33"/>
    </para>
