  <chapter number="13" style="c" sid="MRK 13" />
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="1" style="v" sid="MRK 13:1" />While leaving the temple, one of his disciples <char style="it">then </char>says, “Teacher, look—what
        <char style="it">breathtaking</char> stones and edifices.” <verse eid="MRK 13:1" />
      <verse number="2" style="v" sid="MRK 13:2" />Jesus said to him, <char style="wj">“See these great edifices here? Not a single stone here will remain
        on top of another stone which will not in any way get torn down.”</char> <verse eid="MRK 13:2" />
      <verse number="3" style="v" sid="MRK 13:3" />Sitting across from temple on the Mount of Olives alone with Peter, James, John, and Andrew, <verse eid="MRK 13:3" />
      <verse number="4" style="v" sid="MRK 13:4" />they asked him <char style="it">confidentially</char>, “When will these things take place, and what will
        be the sign<char style="sup">[a]</char> indicating when the conclusion<char style="sup">[b]</char> of
        all things is supposed to happen?” <verse eid="MRK 13:4" />
      <verse number="5" style="v" sid="MRK 13:5" />Jesus began by saying to them, <char style="wj">“See to it that no one gets you off-base; </char><verse eid="MRK 13:5" />
      <verse number="6" style="v" sid="MRK 13:6" /><char style="wj">many will come claiming to have my authority</char><char style="sup">[c]</char><char
        style="wj"> saying, ‘I am </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">the one-and-only one</char></char><char
        style="wj">,’</char><char style="sup">[A]</char><char style="wj"> and many will get off-base. </char><verse eid="MRK 13:6" />
      <verse number="7" style="v" sid="MRK 13:7" /><char style="wj">When you hear about there being wars and news of wars </char><char style="it"><char
        style="wj">that are right around the corner</char></char><char style="wj">, don’t get rattled: </char><char
        style="it"><char style="wj">these things</char></char><char style="wj"> have to happen, but it’s not
        over</char><char style="sup">[d]</char><char style="wj"> yet. </char><verse eid="MRK 13:7" />
      <verse number="8" style="v" sid="MRK 13:8" /><char style="wj">You see, nations and ethnic groups will assert themselves against or attack </char><char
        style="it"><char style="wj">other</char></char><char style="wj"> nations and ethnic groups, and kingdoms
        against kingdoms; there’ll be earthquakes from place to place; there’ll be famines—these are the first
        labor pains. </char><verse eid="MRK 13:8" />
      <verse number="9" style="v" sid="MRK 13:9" /><char style="wj">For your part, look after yourselves; they’ll take you into custody </char><char style="it"><char
        style="wj">and drag you</char></char><char style="wj"> before the local council</char><char style="sup">[B]</char><char
        style="wj">, they’ll work you over</char><char style="sup">[e]</char><char style="wj"> in the synagogues,
        and on account of me you’ll be made to stand before rulers and kings and testify before them. </char><verse eid="MRK 13:9" />
      <verse number="10" style="v" sid="MRK 13:10" /><char style="wj">The Good News</char><char style="sup">[f]</char><char style="wj"> must be proclaimed
        to all the nations and ethnic groups. </char><verse eid="MRK 13:10" />
      <verse number="11" style="v" sid="MRK 13:11" /><char style="wj">When they take you away into custody, don’t worry beforehand what you’ll say, but instead
        what you’re going to say will be given to you the </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">very</char></char><char
        style="wj"> moment </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">it’s needed</char></char><char style="wj">;
        you see, it’s not you who’s doing the talking but rather the Holy Spirit. </char><verse eid="MRK 13:11" />
      <verse number="12" style="v" sid="MRK 13:12" /><char style="wj">A brother will betray a brother to </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">the point
        of</char></char><char style="wj"> death, and a father his son, and children will turn against their parent,
        defy them, and become hostile towards them, and </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">because of this</char></char><char
        style="wj"> they’ll be put to death. </char><verse eid="MRK 13:12" />
      <verse number="13" style="v" sid="MRK 13:13" /><char style="wj">You’ll be hated by everyone on account of you doing what I told you to do</char><char
        style="sup">[g]</char><char style="wj">. He who perseveres until it’s all over—that’s the </char><char
        style="it"><char style="wj">sort of</char></char><char style="wj"> guy who’ll survive.</char><verse eid="MRK 13:13" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="14" style="v" sid="MRK 13:14" /><char style="wj">”When you see the ‘abomination that causes things to fall into desolation</char><char
        style="sup">[h]</char><char style="wj">’—the Prophet Daniel’s prophecy—standing where it shouldn’t (have
        the one who reads this </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">out loud to the congregation</char></char><char
        style="wj"> get up to speed on this </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">ahead of time</char></char><char
        style="wj">)</char><char style="sup">[C]</char><char style="wj">, then have those in Judea flee to the
        mountains. </char><verse eid="MRK 13:14" />
      <verse number="15" style="v" sid="MRK 13:15" /><char style="wj">Don’t have whoever’s on the porch go down, go in, and fetch anything out of the house,</char><char
        style="sup">[D]</char><verse eid="MRK 13:15" />
      <verse number="16" style="v" sid="MRK 13:16" /><char style="wj">and don’t have whoever’s in the field turn around and grab his coat. </char><verse eid="MRK 13:16" />
      <verse number="17" style="v" sid="MRK 13:17" /><char style="wj">Oh, how terrible</char><char style="sup">[i]</char><char style="wj"> it’ll be for women
        at that time who are pregnant or have infants!</char><char style="sup">[E]</char><verse eid="MRK 13:17" />
      <verse number="18" style="v" sid="MRK 13:18" /><char style="wj">Hope to God</char><char style="sup">[j]</char><char style="wj"> that it won’t be wintertime.
        </char><verse eid="MRK 13:18" />
      <verse number="19" style="v" sid="MRK 13:19" /><char style="wj">You see, there’ll be a tremendous amount of suffering, such which hasn’t occurred from
        the beginning of time until now and will never happen again. </char><verse eid="MRK 13:19" />
      <verse number="20" style="v" sid="MRK 13:20" /><char style="wj">If it weren’t for those days having been cut short, then not a single living being</char><char
        style="sup">[k]</char><char style="wj"> would survive; but those days will be cut short on account of
        the Chosen Ones</char><char style="sup">[l]</char><char style="wj">. </char><verse eid="MRK 13:20" />
      <verse number="21" style="v" sid="MRK 13:21" /><char style="wj">At that time, if someone says to you, ‘Look here—the Messiah’ or ‘Here </char><char
        style="it"><char style="wj">he is</char></char><char style="wj">’, don’t believe him, </char><verse eid="MRK 13:21" />
      <verse number="22" style="v" sid="MRK 13:22" /><char style="wj">since false messiahs will come to the forefront and produce great signs</char><char
        style="sup">[a]</char><char style="wj"> and wonders in order to deceive, if possible, the Chosen Ones.
        </char><verse eid="MRK 13:22" />
      <verse number="23" style="v" sid="MRK 13:23" /><char style="wj">Keep your eyes open—I’ve told you this ahead of time.</char><verse eid="MRK 13:23" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="24" style="v" sid="MRK 13:24" /><char style="wj">”More to the point, though, in those days, after that </char><char style="it"><char
        style="wj">ordeal of</char></char><char style="wj"> suffering,</char></para>
    <para style="pi" vid="MRK 13:24"></para>
    <para style="pi" vid="MRK 13:24"><char style="wj">“The sun will go dark,</char></para>
    <para style="pi" vid="MRK 13:24"><char style="wj">And the moon won’t shine.</char><verse eid="MRK 13:24"/>
    </para>
    <para style="pi">
      <verse number="25" style="v" sid="MRK 13:25" /><char style="wj">The stars will be falling out of the sky.</char>
    </para>
    <para style="pi" vid="MRK 13:25"><char style="wj">The wonder and might of those things</char></para>
    <para style="pi" vid="MRK 13:25"><char style="wj">In the sky </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">extending </char></char><char style="wj">into
        heaven will be shaken.</char><verse eid="MRK 13:25"/>
    </para>
    <para style="pi" />    <!-- Spacer line. No verse associated with it. -->
    <para style="m">
      <verse number="26" style="v" sid="MRK 13:26" /><char style="wj">”Then they’ll see the Man</char><char style="sup">[m]</char><char style="wj"> coming
        in the clouds with great might and glory, </char><verse eid="MRK 13:26" />
      <verse number="27" style="v" sid="MRK 13:27" /><char style="wj">and then he will send the angels and will gather his Chosen Ones from every corner of
        the earth, from one side of the planet to another</char><char style="sup">[n]</char><char style="wj">.</char><verse eid="MRK 13:27" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="28" style="v" sid="MRK 13:28" /><char style="wj">”Learn from the example of the fig tree: when its branches become tender and its leaves
        bud, know that summer is right around the corner. </char><verse eid="MRK 13:28" />
      <verse number="29" style="v" sid="MRK 13:29" /><char style="wj">The same thing applies to you: when you </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">finally
        do</char></char><char style="wj"> see these things taking place, understand that it’ll be real soon,
        </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">as it’s</char></char><char style="wj"> right at your doorstep.
        </char><verse eid="MRK 13:29" />
      <verse number="30" style="v" sid="MRK 13:30" /><char style="wj">You can count on what I’m telling you: that very period in the history of mankind</char><char
        style="sup">[o]</char><char style="wj"> won’t go away until all these things come to pass. </char><verse eid="MRK 13:30" />
      <verse number="31" style="v" sid="MRK 13:31" /><char style="wj">The sky and the earth will go away, but my words will never-ever go away.</char><verse eid="MRK 13:31" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="32" style="v" sid="MRK 13:32" /><char style="wj">”But concerning that day and hour (</char><char style="it"><char style="wj">i.e., the
        exact moment</char></char><char style="wj">), nobody knows, neither the angels in heaven nor the Son—</char><char
        style="it"><char style="wj">nobody</char></char><char style="wj"> except for the Father. </char><verse eid="MRK 13:32" />
      <verse number="33" style="v" sid="MRK 13:33" /><char style="wj">See that you’re ready, since you don’t know what the timeframe</char><char style="sup">[p]</char><char
        style="wj"> will be—</char><verse eid="MRK 13:33" />
      <verse number="34" style="v" sid="MRK 13:34" /><char style="wj">like a man who’s frequently on the road, who, when leaving home, left his servants in
        charge of each of his </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">various</char></char><char style="wj">
        </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">estate</char></char><char style="wj"> shops</char><char style="sup">[q]</char><char
        style="wj"> and commanded the doorkeeper to keep watch</char><char style="sup">[F]</char><char style="wj">.
        </char><verse eid="MRK 13:34" />
      <verse number="35" style="v" sid="MRK 13:35" /><char style="wj">So now, stay alert</char><char style="sup">[F]</char><char style="wj">, since you don’t
        know when the estate owner will come, whether </char><char style="it"><char style="wj">it be</char></char><char
        style="wj"> at sunset…whether in the middle of the night…whether just before daybreak…whether at daybreak</char><char
        style="sup">[G]</char><char style="wj">. </char><verse eid="MRK 13:35" />
      <verse number="36" style="v" sid="MRK 13:36" /><char style="wj">May he not come all of a sudden and catch you all asleep. </char><verse eid="MRK 13:36" />
      <verse number="37" style="v" sid="MRK 13:37" /><char style="wj">But the point that I’m making in this story applies to you all as well</char><char style="sup">[r]</char><char
        style="sup">[H]</char><char style="wj">: Stay focused!</char><char style="sup">[F]</char><char style="wj">”</char><verse eid="MRK 13:37" />
    </para>
