  <!--   **********   -->
  <chapter number="15" style="c" sid="MRK 15" />
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="1" style="v" sid="MRK 15:1" />Without delay, late in the night the chief priests, along with all the councilmen and the designated
        teachers<char style="sup">[a]</char>, convened a meeting, bound Jesus, carried him away, and delivered
        him into Pilate’s custody. <verse eid="MRK 15:1" />
      <verse number="2" style="v" sid="MRK 15:2" />Pilate asked him, “You’re the king of the Jews?” He answered him, “Whatever you say<char style="sup">[b]</char>.”<verse eid="MRK 15:2" />
      <verse number="3" style="v" sid="MRK 15:3" />The chief priests accused him of many things. <verse eid="MRK 15:3" />
      <verse number="4" style="v" sid="MRK 15:4" />Again, Pilate asked him, “You’re not going to say anything in response? Take a look at how many accusations
        they’ve leveled against you.” <verse eid="MRK 15:4" />
      <verse number="5" style="v" sid="MRK 15:5" />But to Pilate’s astonishment, Jesus didn’t have anything more to say.<verse eid="MRK 15:5" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="6" style="v" sid="MRK 15:6" />He had an ongoing <char style="it">tradition</char>, done at each festival, of releasing one prisoner
        for them, whomever they’d ask for. <verse eid="MRK 15:6" />
      <verse number="7" style="v" sid="MRK 15:7" />There was one called Barabbas who had been imprisoned along with the revolutionaries<char style="sup">[A]</char>,
        <char style="it">in particular</char> those who had committed murder during the insurrection<char style="sup">[A]</char>.<verse eid="MRK 15:7" />
      <verse number="8" style="v" sid="MRK 15:8" />The crowd came over and initiated making the request, in accordance with his usual practice. <verse eid="MRK 15:8" />
      <verse number="9" style="v" sid="MRK 15:9" />Pilate responded to them, “Do you want me to set the king of the Jews free?”, <verse eid="MRK 15:9" />
      <verse number="10" style="v" sid="MRK 15:10" />since he was aware that the chief priests had him arrested out of envy. <verse eid="MRK 15:10" />
      <verse number="11" style="v" sid="MRK 15:11" />Now, the chief priests had whipped the crowd into a frenzy, in order that their preference would be to
        release Barabbas.<verse eid="MRK 15:11" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="12" style="v" sid="MRK 15:12" />Again, Pilate responded to them,
    </para>
    <para style="p" vid="MRK 15:12">“So now, what do you want me to do with the one who’s called the King of the Jews?”<verse eid="MRK 15:12"/>
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="13" style="v" sid="MRK 15:13" />Again, they shouted, “Crucify him!”<verse eid="MRK 15:13" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="14" style="v" sid="MRK 15:14" />Pilate said to them multiple times, “…Because he’s done what wrong?”
    </para>
    <para style="p" vid="MRK 15:14">But they shouted all the more, “Crucify him!”<verse eid="MRK 15:14"/>
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="15" style="v" sid="MRK 15:15" />Intending to placate the crowd, Pilate set Barabbas free and handed over Jesus, after<char style="it">
        he had him</char> flogged, to be crucified.<verse eid="MRK 15:15" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="16" style="v" sid="MRK 15:16" />The soldiers led him away to a courtyard inside <char style="it">the compound</char>, the one used by
        the governor’s security guards<char style="sup">[c]</char>, and called over the entire company of guards.<verse eid="MRK 15:16" />
      <verse number="17" style="v" sid="MRK 15:17" />They clothed him in a robe a nobleman would wear<char style="sup">[B]</char> and placed on<char style="sup">[d]</char>
        him a crown, a wreath woven from thorns. <verse eid="MRK 15:17" />
      <verse number="18" style="v" sid="MRK 15:18" />They began to go about greeting him, “Pleased <char style="it">to meet you</char><char style="sup">[e]</char>
        King of the Jews.” <verse eid="MRK 15:18" />
      <verse number="19" style="v" sid="MRK 15:19" />They kept on hitting him on the head with a rod, spitting on him, and getting on their knees in an act
        of subservience to him. <verse eid="MRK 15:19" />
      <verse number="20" style="v" sid="MRK 15:20" />When they finished ridiculing him, they took the robe off and put his clothes back on him, and they led
        him away to be crucified<char style="sup">[f]</char>.<verse eid="MRK 15:20" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="21" style="v" sid="MRK 15:21" />They pressed into service a random passerby, Simon of Cyrene (<char style="it">the one who’s the </char>father
        of Alexander and Rufus), who <char style="it">happened to be</char> coming in from <char style="it">working
        out in</char> the fields, to carry<char style="sup">[g]</char> his cross. <verse eid="MRK 15:21" />
      <verse number="22" style="v" sid="MRK 15:22" />They brought him <char style="it">up</char> <char style="it">on</char> <char style="it">top of</char><char
        style="sup">[h]</char> the place called Golgotha, which translated means “Skull Place.” <verse eid="MRK 15:22" />
      <verse number="23" style="v" sid="MRK 15:23" />They kept on <char style="it">trying to</char> give him spiced<char style="sup">[C]</char> wine, but
        he wouldn’t take it. <verse eid="MRK 15:23" />
      <verse number="24" style="v" sid="MRK 15:24" />They crucified him and divvied up his clothing, rolling dice<char style="sup">[i]</char> to see who was
        going <char style="it">to get</char> to take it away. <verse eid="MRK 15:24" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="25" style="v" sid="MRK 15:25" />Now it was mid-morning<char style="sup">[D]</char> when they performed the crucifixion on him.<char style="sup">[j]</char><verse eid="MRK 15:25" />
      <verse number="26" style="v" sid="MRK 15:26" />There was a sign stating the reason <char style="it">why he was crucified</char>, and it read, “The king
        of the Jews.” <verse eid="MRK 15:26" />
      <verse number="27" style="v" sid="MRK 15:27" />They crucified two thugs with him, together as a group, one to the left of him and one to the right of
        him<char style="sup">[k]</char>. <verse eid="MRK 15:27" />
      <verse number="28" style="v" sid="MRK 15:28" /><char style="sup">[l]</char> <verse eid="MRK 15:28" />
      <verse number="29" style="v" sid="MRK 15:29" />Those who passed by reviled him, nodding their heads <char style="it">left and right</char> saying, “Ah!
        The one who’ll <char style="it">supposedly</char> destroy the temple and rebuild it in three days— <verse eid="MRK 15:29" />
      <verse number="30" style="v" sid="MRK 15:30" />Save yourself: come down off that cross.” <verse eid="MRK 15:30" />
      <verse number="31" style="v" sid="MRK 15:31" />In the same way, the chief priests and the designated teachers<char style="sup">[m]</char>, going back
        and forth with each other making fun of him, in the midst of that were saying, “He <char style="it">went
        and</char> rescued others, but he cannot save himself. <verse eid="MRK 15:31" />
      <verse number="32" style="v" sid="MRK 15:32" />The Messiah, the Christ, the King of Israel: let him come down from the cross now, so that we would see
        and believe.” Even his fellow crucifixion-mates kept on taunting him.<verse eid="MRK 15:32" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="33" style="v" sid="MRK 15:33" />When it got to be noon<char style="sup">[D]</char>, darkness appeared over the entire planet until late
        afternoon<char style="sup">[D]</char>, <verse eid="MRK 15:33" />
      <verse number="34" style="v" sid="MRK 15:34" />and in the late afternoon<char style="sup">[D]</char>, Jesus shouted in a loud voice, <char style="wj">“Eloi,
        eloi, lema sabachthani?”</char>, which is translated, <char style="wj">“My God, my God, why have you
        abandoned me?” </char><verse eid="MRK 15:34" />
      <verse number="35" style="v" sid="MRK 15:35" />Some of the bystanders heard this and started saying, “Look, he’s calling on Elijah.” <verse eid="MRK 15:35" />
      <verse number="36" style="v" sid="MRK 15:36" />Someone ran and soaked a sponge in a mixture of water and vinegar that the soldiers commonly drank, put
        it on a rod, and proceeded to <char style="it">offer it</char> to him to drink, saying, “Let’s see if
        Elijah comes and takes him down from off the cross,” <verse eid="MRK 15:36" />
      <verse number="37" style="v" sid="MRK 15:37" />but Jesus let out a great cry and passed away<char style="sup">[n]</char>, <verse eid="MRK 15:37" />
      <verse number="38" style="v" sid="MRK 15:38" />and the temple curtain<char style="sup">[o]</char> was torn in two from top to bottom. <verse eid="MRK 15:38" />
      <verse number="39" style="v" sid="MRK 15:39" />Seeing this, the army captain standing across from him said, “This man really was the embodiment of a
        son<char style="sup">[p]</char> of God.” <verse eid="MRK 15:39" />
      <verse number="40" style="v" sid="MRK 15:40" />Now there were also women watching at a distance, among whom were<char style="sup">[q]</char> Mary Magdalene,
        Mary mother of James the younger and of Joses, and Salome, <verse eid="MRK 15:40" />
      <verse number="41" style="v" sid="MRK 15:41" />those women who were ever his followers and were constantly attending to his needs when he was in Galilee,
        and many other women who accompanied him to Jerusalem.<verse eid="MRK 15:41" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="42" style="v" sid="MRK 15:42" />It had gotten to be late, and since it was a preparatory day (that is, a pre-feast day or pre-Sabbath
        <char style="it">preparatory day</char><char style="sup">[E]</char>), <verse eid="MRK 15:42" />
      <verse number="43" style="v" sid="MRK 15:43" />Joseph of Arimathea, an influential councilman, who also was himself a true believer,<char style="sup">[r]</char>
        got up the courage, entered <char style="it">Pilate’s compound</char>, and went up to Pilate and asked
        for Jesus’s body. <verse eid="MRK 15:43" />
      <verse number="44" style="v" sid="MRK 15:44" />But Pilate wondered if he had <char style="it">in fact</char> died already, and summoned the captain
        and asked him if it had been a while since he died<char style="sup">[s]</char>. <verse eid="MRK 15:44" />
      <verse number="45" style="v" sid="MRK 15:45" />Getting up to speed with the captain, he presented the body to Joseph as a gift, <verse eid="MRK 15:45" />
      <verse number="46" style="v" sid="MRK 15:46" />and Joseph purchased a cloth sheet made of linen and used for wrapping, took him down, rolled him up
        in the sheet, put him in a tomb, one which had been hewn out of a rock <char style="it">formation</char>,
        and rolled a stone over the tomb’s entrance. <verse eid="MRK 15:46" />
      <verse number="47" style="v" sid="MRK 15:47" />Now Mary Magdalene and Mary the mother of Joses were monitoring where he was being placed.<verse eid="MRK 15:47" />
    </para>
